< review>
I really wish I wasn't so bad at taking the pics, and that I had more pizza to share but we all scarfed it down so fast. The pizza here is amazing!! The crust isn't too buttery/airy nor is it too thick, the sauce is tasty not over or underwhelming, they are generous with their toppings, and their cheese is super stretchy. They are very comparable to certain other pizza chains that have a similar chicken bacon garlic pizza only their crust and toppings here are better. The prices are affordable. The staff are friendly as well which is a huge bonus! Also, family friendly and hangout friendly.</review>

< review>
My family and I have eaten 701 pizza for months now.  Frankly, most pizza restaurants sell the same old cardboard pizza with cheap toppings and dough.
I found 701 entirely by accident.  Their pizza crust and toppings are fresh and numerous.  The cheese is plentiful as are the fresh toppings.  For the same price as those flavorless pizza pies, these pizzas are top shelf!  You owe it to yourself to try a real pizza meal, not a cheap pizza!<//review>

< text>
Ordered delivery from here tonight for the first time and chose the Chicken Garlic speciality pizza. It was the worst chicken garlic I've ever had, if not some of the worst pizza I've had in general.. It was basically flavourless? I don't know how else to describe it.. I have had many chicken garlic pizzas from the surrounding area and have never taken a bite and been confused at how flavourless it was, especially with so many toppings on it. My girlfriend and I tried adding salt and dipping it ranch (which you shouldn't really have to do with white sauce pizza) and it was still very very bland. They even go as far as to claim they make the roasted garlic white sauce in house...if that's really true maybe you should just leave the "homemade" part out because it reflects very poorly on the chef, if there even is one for a value priced pizzeria.

It's my take that a lot of these reviews are fake. The grammer is horrible on most of them, and they usually mention things such as the decor on the inside of the pizzeria rather than the quality of the pizza? Many of them even said it was on the " Pricy side, but delicious " on the GrubHub reviews which makes absolutely no sense considering it's cheaper than pizza guys... Yet I am to believe these reviews are real..

On top of everything it arrived room temperature, which was why I thought it tasted bland initially, so we heated it up to proper temp in our oven after the first cold bite and it was still BLAND AS CARDBOARD.

Im really not one to be picky about cheap pizza, but please don't be fooled by the 4.9 star review, this pizza was worse than mediocre at best. Feel free to check my review history, I rarely leave reviews in the first place in the many many years I've had this account and they are almost always positive ones.

I will gladly update this review if the owners feel like the pizza I received was an anomaly and wants to make it right. Otherwise, just order from Pizza Guys if you want cheap pizza, at least it's flavorful.<//text>

< text>
Hooray!  I no longer have to be an "Ink Nazi" (as my daughter has called me) since now that I've been using tomatoink we can print what we want and in the colors we want.  I have the best printer I've ever used and absolutely love it but the ink was nearly $20 per cartridge...and it takes 5 to print!!  But I just placed my third order with tomatoink and I realized I've still spent less with them ordering about 12 cartridges than 2 or 3 would've cost in the stores. I have signed the contract to drop my dog off for 22 nights boarding in which my dog would get every other day of tiny tot camp during her boarding. However, on the day prior to boarding day, we paid for her try out at the tiny camp, she was a little over tired when we picked her up. So I spoke with the staff and determined that my dog would still have every other day of exercise, but half of the times would be at the tiny tot camp ($22/day), and half of the time would be a 1 hour play ($12/day). After 22 days, when I picked her up, I was charged for 12 days of tiny tot camp. In fact, I should be charged 6 days of tiny tot camp and 6 days of 1 hour play. I was too jetlag after my such a long flight to deal with it. So I paid $1,056 for the bill. On the next day, I called and explained the situation to the staff, she put me on hold, then came saying that my contract was locked due to the corporate monthly closing. She will have the Manager to call me back on Monday. When the manager (Lindsey, I believe that's her name) called me back she said "I heard you want to talk to me", then I explained the situation with her again. She told me that she was kind of know the staff that did my contract, and that she will have that person called me back on the next day. I waited for 3 days, then I called the store again asked to speak to Lindsey, but she was not there. She then proceeded to ask if I remember the name of the staff who prepared the contract for me. I didn't believe that she asked me that again, so I described the lady with a bit of reddish/dark brown hair, and I said that I would know her when I go to the store again. <user_id>104827645476768493523< /user_id><name>Master Mind<//name><date>1375758455074</date><rate>1</rate>< Review>
I boarded my dog, Buddy, over the weekend, from Friday, August 2 through Monday morning, August 5.  When I picked up the dog I was given a ‚Äúreport card‚Äù that talked about what a sweet dog Buddy was, etc.  Everything on the report was positive.

I waited for quite some time for the attendant to retrieve Buddy.  In fact, while I waited two other clients came, retrieved their dogs, and left.

When Buddy was delivered to me, he was clearly upset.  He would not let the young lady near him to change his collar and put on his leash.  He growled at her whenever she came near him.  The young lady also told me about the ‚Äúsmell‚Äù of Buddy, and said it was because he was so upset.  She mentioned that sometimes she had to use a pole to reach the dog and pull him out of the cage.  I assume she was talking about Buddy.  She also told me that Buddy would probably ‚Äúnot board well‚Äù in the future.

I put the collar and leash on the dog, and we left.  Once in the car, he immediately began to settle down, and began to return to his own personality, which is friendly and playful.

I firmly believe that the dog was mistreated at this facility, and was possibly abused.  I have no proof of that, but am a pretty good judge of character.  Unfortunately, being caught off guard and by surprise, I do not have the name of the young lady, but do recall what she looked like.

I recommend avoiding this place.< /Review>

< rating>
5< /rating>
< text>
We have had Paula and the Mobile Grooming truck come to our house for our 18 lb cat, Spot, for well over a year now. She has done wonders with him when no other groomer could. Previous groomers had actually asked us not to bring Spot in again. Spot came to us as an adult rescued cat. He is a good kitty but he is easily frightened. Paula has the phenomenal ability to calm him and manage him kindly and effectively. We are forever grateful for her compassion and her skills. His long thick fur tends to get matted if he isn't groomed properly. She does an excellent job and somehow even gets a bow on him. The mobile grooming approach coming to our home keeps Spot calm and is worth every penny. We highly recommend Paula and Riverside Pet Grooming.<//text>

This is a great place to eat, very reasonable prices and the portions are perfect, you don't get over stuffed with a lot of food just satisfied. My husband says they have the best Chile rellano and I always order the crispy shredded beef or ground  meat taco which is very good.  The only thing is that the chips are not complimentary it's  $2.50 or so for a very small bowl of chips. Other than that it's a great place to eat.</Text>

<user_name>Hans Robles<//user_name><user>110401490640000113813<//user></record></dataset><record>
<UserId.>101888741039196133682< /UserId.>< user_name>
Daddy B.<//user_name>
< time>
1399598667757</time>
<rate>2<//rate>< review>
Summary: Don't let the authentic decor fool you.  Nothing is what it seems.  When you walk in, you must order at a counter and seat yourself.  When the food arrives, you'll be unimpressed.

Detailed review:

Ordering: when we arrived we were impressed with the authentic-ish Mexican decor but soon realized that was about authentic as it was going to get.  We encountered the chattiest (and loudest) waitress loudly joking with a cook, who took our order.  After ordering, she handed us two drink cups (I ordered a bottle of water).  Assuming the second drink cup was for ice for my bottle of water, my wife grabbed the cup and began filling it with ice.  The waitress actually wanted the cup back and told us she normally charges for the cup. (Wtf?!) As my wife reluctantly handed over the cup, I stopped her and said "too bad, she handed us the cup and now I want it."

Meal:  my wife ordered taquitos (ala carte) and I ordered the chile verde dinner.  The waitress returned and served us within 2 minutes if sitting down.  (Fast = pre cooked). It immediately became clear that the taquitos were store bought frozen, microwaved and served with cheese and freshly chopped lettuce and tomatoes.  The chile verde quickly became apparent that the meat was CANNED, not fresh.  Not even cooked last week - CANNED!  The beans had a bit of a sour aftertaste (possibly mixed in with old beans) and they too suspiciously tasted canned.  The rice was made there, but tasted a day old and reheated in a microwave.

Pluses:  in this mess I found the best damn guacamole I've had in years, and the sauce (chile) used to make the chile verde, was damn good.  They obviously make the salsa themselves and add it to their dishes and guacamole --

Verdict:  if you want fast and tasty (as least for the chilito they serve), then this is for you.  If you expect REAL comida Mexicana hecho fresco y a mano, go somewhere else.  Oh, and if you HATE paying for canned meat and frozen primary ingredients, then this isn't the place you!

We won't be returning.<//review>

<text>Consistently exceptional service and good food. The price is a little higher than some of the other buffets available in the valley, but I think you definitely get your money's worth for it. Plates are cleared and drinks refilled quickly. Food selection may not be as large as say, Morongo, but there's still more than enough to get 3+ plates and still not have repeats on food. Plus the dessert selection is great and all of it is good. I've been with family for both the Prime Rib dinner and for a regular dinner and both occasions were great experiences. I'd actually recommend going on the regular dinners: you save 5 bucks a person, it's not as busy, and they still have strip loin from the carving station so you're not totally without a solid meat option.< /text>< GmapID>

<user_id>107049473546957369512</user_id><Name>Marlene<//Name><Time>1552960047075< /Time><rating>1< /rating>< Text>
We go to this buffet quite often but I will not ever return here again. The service is always great and staff is friendly but last night, my bf and I were eating here. I started with a salad and then went back to the "Mexican food" area for some jalapenos and there was a cockroach crawling along the side of the rice!! At first, I thought it was a fly, so I waved my hand to make it go away but I soon realized it was definitely not a fly. I looked over to the right and there was another one crawling up the counter. I rushed back to our table to tell my bf that there were roaches on the food!! He wanted to see for himself so I took him back to where I saw them but they weren't there anymore. We walked around and sure enough, as we were standing in front of the chocolate fountain, a roach was crawling on the floor towards the counter. I felt so sick to my stomach. I asked for a manager and explained what I saw. She did not seem shocked to say the least. She apologized multiple times and said thank you for letting me know where you saw them. She also offered us a free meal for next time. I told her we would absolutely never eat here again and wanted our money back. She refunded us without incident. Did it matter where we saw them? They were roaches, if I saw 3 within 15 minutes of being there then they are everywhere!! She should have asked everyone to leave and refunded them and fumigated immediately. There was obviously an active roach infestation. I now wish I would have taken pictures but I was so disgusted and just wanted to get out of there. I have since contacted the casino via email and waiting for a reply. I was and still am so disgusted. Yuck!!!< /Text>

102793907158072711395<//user_id>
<Name>Jodi Wagner</Name><Date>1544157385853< /Date><Rate>3</Rate>< Text>
My husband and I visited Coachella Valley for a few days and decided on dining at the Fresh Grill Buffet for dinner, based on the Yelp ratings. We've dined at several casino buffets throughout So Cal and Las Vegas over the years. The overall presentation of the various dishes was appealing and all of the trays were amply stocked for guests to fill their plates. But I can only rate the taste of the food and variety of selection at the Fresh Grill Buffet as "average" (nothing to wow your palate). We did notice that the temperature of the hot dishes were tepid, and quickly lost all heat by the time we sat down to our table to eat our meal. The staff were friendly and quick to respond to our requests. However, although several staff stopped at our table to remove used plates and bowls, no one seemed to notice or bothered to ask if I wanted a refill on my drink (my glass of iced tea remained empty for nearly half an hour after we began our meal and stayed empty when we finished our meal and left the restaurant). Also, through no direct fault of the restaurant, it certainly would help guests enjoy their meals more if the casino ventilation was more effective in reducing the strong smell of cigarette smoke in the air. My sinuses were overly congested and eyes stung and teared a bit. I also noticed a man holding a handkerchief over his nose and mouth as he exited the restaurant to rush up the escalators to the parking garage.< /Text>

Nightmare of an experience.  I initially scheduled an appointment at the hawthorne location but they couldn't do the alignment.  They said the Torrance store could accommodate.  I called them on my way there and I scheduled a 10am appointment and said to ask for Jose.  I got jermaine to greet me and then said it would be a wait when I arrived at 945.  It was 1230 and the car was still not worked on so I left. They said they'd call when it's done and so 4pm rolls around and I come back to find the car done.  jermaine gave me the keys and I drove off to find that my steering wheel is now 5+ degrees off. So I'm driving with a crooked steering wheel.  I come back minutes later for Jermaine to tell me that the results on the sheet show it's fixed.  I had to force him to do a ride along in the drive way and he agreed the steering wheel was crooked and off.  He stated that Erick who worked on the car is struggling and that he might not be able to fix it.  I've done plenty of alignments and someone either didn't have the steering whee straight when doing the front end alignment or the results are just completely off.  jermain then had me wait and said I can come back Monday to get it fixed since the mechanic that they trust and normally use is at another location.  At first I was calm and was wondering why they would put someone not experienced in place to fix cars.  I waited an hour and he said the chances of my car getting fixed is slim.  It's ridiculous at this point and he agreed that I was better off not getting my car aligned.  Another customer came in and began to curse and yell and I can tell Jermaine was having a rough day.  I didn't want to add further stress to the situation and still in a monotone fashion I asked for solutions.  He said I can get an alignment somewhere else and they MIGHT pay for it if it's under 90 bucks or come back Monday.  I live in San Diego and I have a lifetime warranty on alignment, so coming back on a Monday isn't an the best option since I'm in town visiting family.  I think when the tech adjusted the toe on the front end suspension, he incorrectly adjusted the tie rod making the steering wheel off center. An easy fix, jack up the car and loosen the bolts and adjust the tie rod.  The end result is he called Juanita at the sunset location since they had special hours on Sunday for a grand opening and asked that I can get service tomorrow (Sunday) and said for me to go there. I asked if I can get it in writing and he said he couldn't do that, so basically I have to go on word of mouth.  jermaine accuses me then of saying he's a lier when he stated the call to her on his personal cell phone wasn't good enough, I then stated I have no recourse for me to leave the store and go to another location for them to fix it - how am I to prove that there was something wrong and on top of that everything on the ATD website states the store is closed on a Sunday!  At that point I gave up, I came in at 10am, and it's 530pm and my car is not how it was when it came in.  It's crazy to think that everything was done by word of mouth and professionalism and common courtesy was no where to be found.  The automotive bureau is getting a call and the only proof I have is the recorded conversation between jermaine and myself.  Him stating the car was off, that the technician was struggling, and that I'm better off going somewhere else. I'm tryin to comprehend how this is now a problem that his tone and demeanor made it seem like I need to fix.  I'm sure they do their jobs but have some consistency and courtesy for all customers.   Imagine going to a mechanic to do a fix and they make it worse and tell you they'll have to fix it some other time and you'll need to drive carefully for the next few days. Talk about a liability issue.

< review>
I would highly recommend Varsity. I moved to CA from Manhattan (NYC) and had to learn how to drive at a ripe age!  I did a careful research on line before I picked Varsity (Irvine) based on reviews, instructor profiles and the smooth communication with the scheduling office. I took about 30 lessons with Varsity over the course of 2.5 months and received my driver‚Äôs license at first try.  I followed up with a few lessons to improve on freeway driving.
The administration/scheduling office is very competent and incredibly efficient and responsive. They explained the process of getting the license, helped me set up a packed schedule, and were great in accommodating changes.  They are excellent and very organized in communicating schedule and sending lesson reminders.
I had the pleasure of meeting many of the Varsity instructors - all incredibly knowledgeable and professional, each with their style, insights and advice that were remarkably helpful. Each instructor explained things very well and in ways that clicked, and I will remember. A big shout-out and huge thank you to Isaac and Jose with whom I had the most lessons! A big thank you to Michelle, Arturo, Daisy, Kam George, and everyone else. George was a wonderful positive calm presence for the test. I very rarely (almost never) write reviews, but realized how helpful other people‚Äôs reviews of driving schools were for me, so here you go.< /review>

<rating>5</rating>< Review>
I scheduled all appointments at once, and it was easy to do so over the phone. Not too expensive, and they were on time every day. I took 3 2-hr courses, and had a different instructor every time, which turned out to be helpful because each one gave their individual input. All instructors were professional, kind, and very helpful. I could sense that they trusted my driving abilities and were always ready to help and correct me. They gave me constructive criticisms and praise when appropriate. The cars they brought were all decent: similar in style, ability to pump up seats & adjust mirrors etc. to my liking, and easy to use. On the first day, I practiced everything besides freeway driving. During the next two sessions, they took me [of course I drove] by the Laguna Hills DMV, and I got to drive through the drive test course a few times each day, which helped a lot!! They even kept score as I went, and gave me feedback during and after each drive through. My drive test was essentially identical to what I practiced with the instructors, and I passed effortlessly! I appreciated that each instructor also gave me a few minutes long break after the first hour. They ensured that I reached home exactly when my lesson was over. I felt safe driving with them, and didn't encounter any issues with the personnel or vehicles.
Walter was one of my favorite instructors, he gave me confidence in my abilities and made me far less hesitant to drive at the speed limit. < review>
I work a lot of hours and had to find a school that could teach my daughter how to drive and take her out enough to really learn how to negotiate Orange County roads.  So I signed her up for the Varsity Driving Academy their 20+ hour behind-the-wheel package.  They took her driving booth in the daytime and at night, which gave her the confidence and experience to pass the DMV driving test the first time.

Additionally, the office staff is very helpful.  We especially liked Ms. Katie Korona, who helped us pick the right package to meet our needs.  She also coordinated a driving schedule that worked extremely well with my daughters‚Äô availability.  Her customer services skills are exceptional.

Our favorite instructor ‚ÄúGeorge‚Äù has nerves of steel, and nothing fazes him.  I personally could not handle the experience of having my daughter behind the wheel.  She was not very good at first.  After a few classes with him, she improved immensely.  George is very good at pointing out why one needs to follow certain driving rules on the freeway versus streets.  This is really important because explaining the reasoning behind certain rules of the road (DMV) helps a student remember it when it comes time to drive and to take the DMV driving test.  His straightforward manner really helped my daughter improve her driving skills.   With all the accidents I witness every day driving home in traffic, I am so grateful to George and the other instructors for giving my daughter the driving skills to hopefully avoid being in an accident.  They took her onto the 22 freeway, the 55 freeway (which is known for its daily quota of accidents) and the 405 freeway several times so she would have the skills necessary to drive on them.  My daughter got her license but wanted a few extra lessons on dealing with nighttime traffic on the freeway, so I signed her up for 6 more hours.  This has been an excellent investment.  The night time driving teachers are also great and since most of them are at the high traffic hours, my daughter got the skills and confidence to help her feel better about driving in traffic.

As for the cars, they are each a  bit different in size, which is great.  My daughter learned about the differences between the vehicles and how they can affect how she changes lanes (in heavy traffic) and the different blind spots.  Varsity Driving Academy really took the time out to plan an excellent driving sessions for my daughter to help her learn the skills she needed to drive in Orange County.  I would recommend this program to any parent who is nervous about their child driving in Orange County or who want the best possible instructors for their child.</review>

If you're looking for a driver's ed class, then look no further. After just finishing the four day in-class program, I do not have a single doubt about their high quality way of teaching you to be a safe driver. VDA excels in helping you master the basics of operating a motor vehicle, and they do this by the sample assessments that you take in abundance, the videos they show you in class, and the very informative teacher that helps you throughout.

The first taste I got of VDA was when I called to set myself up to join the in-class program. I spoke on the phone with Caitlin, who made my sign-up was really easy. She was very friendly on the phone, and I was surprised by how smooth the sign-up process went.
This helped jump start my excitement to be at VDA.

Katie was my teacher and will be my driving instructor when I pass the written test. Katie answered all the questions I had, at the highest degree of knowledge. She was very friendly and very approachable, and you are able to ask her any kind of question, no matter how stupid you may think the question is. Katie is, without a doubt, the greatest teacher you will find.

And for Mark, the owner, was no stranger to the friendliness that engulfs you as you start to be involved with VDA. His demeanor was very impressive. You'd expect that the owner would tend to other more important duties, but Mark was there because he wanted to be, and that was very easy to sense. He would contribute a lot to the discussions we had in class and he was a very easy person to speak to. Mark had a great presence, and it was also great to hear what he had to say. He always had something useful to say, and just his general attitude was great.

As a whole, VDA's environment was very friendly. Oftentimes, the driving instructors would pass through and they all added to the friendly environment. You could easily tell that the people were there because they wanted to be there. They are strategically located next to a shopping center, so you could eat out during lunch time. That's if they don't fill you up with the box of chocolates that they pass around. VDA is an elite driver's education establishment, and there is no place like it.

To conclude, I do not usually make an effort to write a review for a place. However, I made an exception today. The reason I made that exception, is that VDA is exceptional.

No, but seriously. VDA.< /Review>
